Earlier this evening, the sinister Lanys T'vyl reared her head in Oasis, calling forth all supporters of the Teir'Dal to aid her once more. It seems she is interested in yet another personal quest, but slickly worded as if it was for the greater good of all Teir'Dals and their allies. Similar to her first defeat in Bloody Kithicor, Lanys is willing to throw away the lives of those loyal to her so that she may gain.<br>
<br>
A large crowd of inquisitive travelers and followers gathered closely around her, while forces of light cautiously watched from the outskirts of the group. Lanys informed everyone that she was after an item called the Eye of Judgement. It was one of three components needed to piece together the Governor of the Wicked, a staff supposedly much more powerful than the one Firiona Vie once held, Lifeguide. The Teir’Dal owned the staff for eons, but valiant Knights from the Hall of Truth obtained it, corrupted and altered its powers, broke it into 3 pieces, then dispersed it across Norrath.<br>
<br>
Lanys then said that the Eye of Judgement could be found on Nyaphet Sijer, a Sphinx located in the Rathe Mountains. She lead her group of followers on their journey towards the Rathe Mountains, while the forces of light who listened in made their own party in hopes of thwarting her plans.<br>
<br>
When both parties arrived in the Rathe Mountains, trackers found Nyaphet waiting by the beetle pillar. Originally, the Lightbearers were anticipating a battle in order to protect Nyaphet Sijer from Lanys, but he would have of that, for he was overconfident in his own strengths.<br>
<br>
After brushing off the Lightbearers, Nyaphet offered the Eye of Judgement to Lanys if she could play his game by solving a riddle. If the answer were wrong, she would pay with her life. Lanys, feigning confidence, opted to choose a champion to answer for her anyway. Many desperate volunteers begged to champion Lanys T'vyl, and she finally chose a young Ogre named Dhast. Good and evil alike doubted his wisdom and did not think he would have the capacity to solve the riddle, but they were wrong, and Dhast solved it easily. Despite the Lightbearers protests and threats to what was happening, Nyaphet regretfully honored her side of the agreement by removing her right eye out of its socket and handing it to Lanys. Some Lightbearers at this point tried attacking Nyaphet and Lanys, but found that they were unable to. Lanys awarded Dhast for his efforts by naming him Dhast the Discerning. Lanys then went off to study the Eye of Judgement some more, stating that she would be back when the time was right to pursue the second piece of the staff.&quot;<br>
